@KelseyTuoc @geekethics @sonyasupposedly I mean, here's how I'm reading this study:

1) throw out the control group; it's genuinely worse than useless as described — for all we know, they always wore a medical mask in close contact with the sick

2) conclude that medical masks work better than cloth masks — makes sense!

@KelseyTuoc @sonyasupposedly I think "30% hurts" is *really* high.

No study is perfect, but the one everyone is passing around does not, in any meaningful sense, have a control group.

Second, looking at health workers who'd be at high risk even in full PPE w/ decontamination protocols doesn't tell us much.
